</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0244-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0244-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>For the approval of Jacob Bayleys road, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-04-02-0176" class="document">GWs second letter to Hancock of 5 May</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-04-02-0205" class="document">Hancock to GW, 10 May 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-04-02-0244-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-04-02-0244-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>Congress approved these resolutions on 14 May (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Worthington Chauncey Ford et al., eds. &lt;i&gt;Journals of the Continental Congress, 1774-1789&lt;/i&gt;. 34 vols. Washington, D.C., 190437. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">JCC</span></span>, 4:35556; see also <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-04-02-0252" class="document">Massachusetts Delegates to GW, 16 May 1776</a>).</p>

